</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF31D6C0FFC2FF82FF109CCF3B329DEA" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443633" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5443633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443633/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="345" startId="19.[144,234,1441,1460]" targetBox="[369,1198,202,1411]" targetPageId="19">
<paragraph id="8BF18648FFC2FF82FF109CCF3B329DEA" blockId="19.[144,1421,1441,1489]" pageId="19" pageNumber="345">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC2FF82FF109CCF3B469D8F" bold="true" box="[144,310,1441,1460]" pageId="19" pageNumber="345">Figures 65–68.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C4EFDCBFFC2FF82FEC29CCF387D9D8F" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1887" box="[322,525,1441,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="345" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallicus">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC2FF82FEC29CCF387D9D8F" box="[322,525,1441,1460]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="345">Tegyrius metallicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 65, prosternum; 66, meso- and metasternum, and pleurites; 67, mesendosternite; 68, metendosternite.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BF18648FFC2FF82FF109FED382E9ECF" blockId="19.[144,759,1667,1903]" pageId="19" pageNumber="345">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC2FF82FF109FED3B689EA3" box="[144,280,1667,1688]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="345">Description:</emphasis>
General colour black. Antennae and legs light brown, with or without rufous tinge; metafemora, and often ventral side of metatibia, piceous. Elytra with indistinct green metallic reflection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF18648FFC2FF82FF289F933F239E60" blockId="19.[144,759,1667,1903]" lastBlockId="19.[806,1421,1544,1903]" pageId="19" pageNumber="345">Supraorbital sulcus distinct. Third antennomere slightly shorter than fourth; fourth shorter or subequal to fifth; sixth shorter than fifth, and subequal to third; antennomeres 7–10 each slightly shorter than the preceding one; first subequal to last. Distal antennomeres not appreciably thickened; antennae reach half of the pronotum over the elytra or beyond.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF18648FFC2FF85FCBF9F0A3BD89ECF" blockId="19.[806,1421,1544,1903]" lastBlockId="20.[164,779,1728,1903]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="346" pageId="19" pageNumber="345">Pronotum with antebasal transverse impression, and with punctures in the antebasal transverse impression not stronger than those on rest of the pronotum. Apex of intercoxal prosternal precess convex, with two preapical depressions. Prosternal intercoxal process 3.1 times wider than the distance between the anterior margin of the prosternum and the coxal cavity; distance from the anterior margin of the prosternum to the end of the intercoxal prosternal process 2.0 times the minimum width of the prosternal intercoxal process.</paragraph>
<caption id="DF31D6C0FFC5FF85FF249F3D3F6E9EBF" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443635" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5443635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443635/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="346" startId="20.[164,254,1619,1638]" targetBox="[323,1281,195,1587]" targetPageId="20">
<paragraph id="8BF18648FFC5FF85FF249F3D3F6E9EBF" blockId="20.[164,1441,1619,1668]" pageId="20" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC5FF85FF249F3D3B3A9E5D" bold="true" box="[164,330,1619,1638]" pageId="20" pageNumber="346">Figures 69–75.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C4EFDCBFFC5FF85FED69F3A38569E5D" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1887" box="[342,550,1619,1638]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallicus">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC5FF85FED69F3A38569E5D" box="[342,550,1619,1638]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="346">Tegyrius metallicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 69, metanotum; 70, intercoxal ridges on first abdominal ventrite; 71, male last abdominal ventrite; 72, aedeagus, ventral view; 73, aedeagus, lateral view; 74, distal opening; 75, tegmen.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BF18648FFC5FF85FF3C9F9339AE9F54" blockId="20.[164,779,1728,1903]" lastBlockId="20.[826,1441,1728,1903]" pageId="20" pageNumber="346">Mesoscutellum broader than long, with broadly rounded apex. Mesosternal intercoxal process transversely depressed in anterior half, posterior margin concave. Elytra with maximum width at middle; elytral apex concave, moderately broad; elytral punctures weak, and tend to form rows, with the distance between the adjacent punctures 1–3 times the diameter of a puncture in the anterior half of the elytra. First metatarsomere longer than half of the metatibia.</paragraph>
<caption id="DF31D6C0FFC4FF84FF109D0A3E6B9C4C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443637" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5443637" box="[144,1051,1124,1144]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443637/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="347" startId="21.[144,234,1124,1143]" targetBox="[303,1261,197,1091]" targetPageId="21">
<paragraph id="8BF18648FFC4FF84FF109D0A3E6B9C4C" blockId="21.[144,1051,1124,1144]" box="[144,1051,1124,1144]" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC4FF84FF109D0A3B469C4C" bold="true" box="[144,310,1124,1143]" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">Figures 76–78.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C4EFDCBFFC4FF84FEC29D0B387F9C4C" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1887" box="[322,527,1124,1143]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallicus">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC4FF84FEC29D0B387F9C4C" box="[322,527,1124,1143]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">Tegyrius metallicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 76, spermatheca; 77, vaginal palpi; 78, tignum.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BF18648FFC4FF84FF289DF738EC9DBE" blockId="21.[144,759,1177,1903]" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">
Subparallel ridges on the first abdominal ventrite well developed, with a row of setae, extending beyond two-thirds of the ventrite, and almost parallel to each other distally (
<figureCitation id="13759ACDFFC4FF84FEBC9D9B3BFE9D30" box="[316,398,1269,1291]" captionStart="Figures 69–75" captionStartId="20.[164,254,1619,1638]" captionTargetBox="[323,1281,195,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-81@20.[323,1283,193,1589]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figures 69–75. Tegyrius metallicus: 69, metanotum; 70, intercoxal ridges on first abdominal ventrite; 71, male last abdominal ventrite; 72, aedeagus, ventral view; 73, aedeagus, lateral view; 74, distal opening; 75, tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443635/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
). Lobe in middle of last visible ventrite of males unique in being granulate, without long setae, and bearing longitudinal ridges on either side, with a concave apical margin (
<figureCitation id="13759ACDFFC4FF84FDD79C3F38D89D5C" box="[599,680,1361,1383]" captionStart="Figures 69–75" captionStartId="20.[164,254,1619,1638]" captionTargetBox="[323,1281,195,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-81@20.[323,1283,193,1589]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figures 69–75. Tegyrius metallicus: 69, metanotum; 70, intercoxal ridges on first abdominal ventrite; 71, male last abdominal ventrite; 72, aedeagus, ventral view; 73, aedeagus, lateral view; 74, distal opening; 75, tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443635/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
). Last female tergite without a longitudinal groove.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF18648FFC4FF84FF289CE03B069E60" blockId="21.[144,759,1177,1903]" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">
Aedeagus distinctly curved in the middle, with straight ends in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="13759ACDFFC4FF84FE629CC238439DF8" box="[482,563,1452,1475]" captionStart="Figures 69–75" captionStartId="20.[164,254,1619,1638]" captionTargetBox="[323,1281,195,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-81@20.[323,1283,193,1589]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figures 69–75. Tegyrius metallicus: 69, metanotum; 70, intercoxal ridges on first abdominal ventrite; 71, male last abdominal ventrite; 72, aedeagus, ventral view; 73, aedeagus, lateral view; 74, distal opening; 75, tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443635/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
); in ventral view, apex broad, without angulate extremities, and with lateral edges distinctly raised, with a depressed area in between (
<figureCitation id="13759ACDFFC4FF84FEA09F663B019E25" box="[288,369,1544,1566]" captionStart="Figures 69–75" captionStartId="20.[164,254,1619,1638]" captionTargetBox="[323,1281,195,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-81@20.[323,1283,193,1589]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figures 69–75. Tegyrius metallicus: 69, metanotum; 70, intercoxal ridges on first abdominal ventrite; 71, male last abdominal ventrite; 72, aedeagus, ventral view; 73, aedeagus, lateral view; 74, distal opening; 75, tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443635/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">Fig. 72</figureCitation>
); distal opening partially covered by lamina (
<figureCitation id="13759ACDFFC4FF84FE9B9F493B1C9E06" box="[283,364,1575,1597]" captionStart="Figures 69–75" captionStartId="20.[164,254,1619,1638]" captionTargetBox="[323,1281,195,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-81@20.[323,1283,193,1589]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figures 69–75. Tegyrius metallicus: 69, metanotum; 70, intercoxal ridges on first abdominal ventrite; 71, male last abdominal ventrite; 72, aedeagus, ventral view; 73, aedeagus, lateral view; 74, distal opening; 75, tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443635/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
); arms of tegmen slightly longer than stem (
<figureCitation id="13759ACDFFC4FF84FE989F2B3B199E60" box="[280,361,1605,1627]" captionStart="Figures 69–75" captionStartId="20.[164,254,1619,1638]" captionTargetBox="[323,1281,195,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-81@20.[323,1283,193,1589]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figures 69–75. Tegyrius metallicus: 69, metanotum; 70, intercoxal ridges on first abdominal ventrite; 71, male last abdominal ventrite; 72, aedeagus, ventral view; 73, aedeagus, lateral view; 74, distal opening; 75, tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443635/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">Fig. 75</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF18648FFC4FF84FF289F0A3BE99F54" blockId="21.[144,759,1177,1903]" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">
Spermatheca with smoothly curved pump, receptacle about 2.5 times longer than broad, inner side convex, outer side concave, gradually narrowing towards duct, and with the duct highly knotted (
<figureCitation id="13759ACDFFC4FF84FF189FB03A9A9ECF" box="[152,234,1758,1780]" captionStart="Figures 76–78" captionStartId="21.[144,234,1124,1143]" captionTargetBox="[303,1261,197,1091]" captionTargetId="figure-329@21.[303,1263,194,1094]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figures 76–78. Tegyrius metallicus: 76, spermatheca; 77, vaginal palpi; 78, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443637/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">Fig. 76</figureCitation>
). Vaginal palpus with distal sclerotization longer than proximal sclerotization, and with proximal sclerotization subequal to the lateral membranous area (
<figureCitation id="13759ACDFFC4FF84FEAF9E543BF09F6B" box="[303,384,1850,1872]" captionStart="Figures 76–78" captionStartId="21.[144,234,1124,1143]" captionTargetBox="[303,1261,197,1091]" captionTargetId="figure-329@21.[303,1263,194,1094]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figures 76–78. Tegyrius metallicus: 76, spermatheca; 77, vaginal palpi; 78, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443637/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
). Tignum with broad distal sclerotization (
<figureCitation id="13759ACDFFC4FF84FEBB9E373BFC9F54" box="[315,396,1881,1903]" captionStart="Figures 76–78" captionStartId="21.[144,234,1124,1143]" captionTargetBox="[303,1261,197,1091]" captionTargetId="figure-329@21.[303,1263,194,1094]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figures 76–78. Tegyrius metallicus: 76, spermatheca; 77, vaginal palpi; 78, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443637/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF18648FFC4FF84FCA69DF739AA9DBE" blockId="21.[806,1421,1177,1413]" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC4FF84FCA69DF73E619C95" box="[806,1041,1177,1198]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">Sexual dimorphism:</emphasis>
First pro- and mesotarsomeres slightly enlarged in males. Ventrally, first protarsomere with minute, bud-like sensilla in males, and with short, pointed setae in females. Ventromesal side of first metatarsomere with a shiny patch of short, capitate setae in males; in females, only pointed plumose setae present on ventral side of first metatarsomere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF18648FFC4FF84FCA69CD339CA9F38" blockId="21.[806,1421,1468,1796]" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC4FF84FCA69CD33E439DEA" box="[806,1075,1468,1490]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="347">Measurements (n = 4):</emphasis>
Length, 2.26–2.62 (2.42); width, 1.28–1.51 (1.37); length of pronotum, 0.52–0.65 (0.57); width of pronotum, 0.78–0.94 (0.84); width of head across eyes, 0.59–0.68 (0.63); transverse diameter of one eye, 0.24–0.27 (0.26); distance between eyes, 0.27–0.30 (0.28); distance between eye and antennal socket, 0.02–0.04 (0.03); distance between antennal sockets, 0.07–0.09 (0.08); diameter of one antennal socket, 0.07–0.08 (0.08); length of aedeagus, 0.95; length of receptacle, 0.26; length of vaginal palpus, 0.42.
</paragraph>
