<taxonomicNameLabel id="A209E721FFC7FF87FEF59B743BBB9A14" box="[373,459,538,559]" pageId="22" pageNumber="348" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be differentiated easily from 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EFDCBFFC7FF87FF629B563B049A76" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1887" box="[226,372,568,589]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallicus">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC7FF87FF629B563B049A76" box="[226,372,568,589]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="348">T. metallicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the structure of the subparallel ridges on the first abdominal ventrite, and by the genitalia. Subparallel ridges converge and completely fuse distally in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EFDCBFFC7FF87FEEE9BFA3B839A92" authority="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath, 2009" authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" box="[366,499,660,681]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buddhai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC7FF87FEEE9BFA3B839A92" box="[366,499,660,681]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="348">T. buddhai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A209E721FFC7FF87FD829BFA38109A92" box="[514,608,660,681]" pageId="22" pageNumber="348" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(whereas the ridges are nearly parallel in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EFDCBFFC7FF87FE679BDD38089AFC" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1887" box="[487,632,690,712]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallicus">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC7FF87FE679BDD38089AFC" box="[487,632,690,712]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="348">T. metallicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The aedeagus in ventral view in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EFDCBFFC7FF87FE249BBF38509ADD" authority="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath, 2009" authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" box="[420,544,721,742]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buddhai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC7FF87FE249BBF38509ADD" box="[420,544,721,742]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="348">T. buddhai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A209E721FFC7FF87FDA89BBF380D9ADD" box="[552,637,721,742]" pageId="22" pageNumber="348" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
lacks ridges along the lateral margins (the lateral margins are raised, forming distinct ridges in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EFDCBFFC7FF87FDE69A61388B9B18" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1887" box="[614,763,782,804]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallicus">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC7FF87FDE69A61388B9B18" box="[614,763,782,804]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="348">T. metallicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the outer side of the spermathecal receptacle is convex (concave in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EFDCBFFC7FF87FE309A2238379B5B" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1887" box="[432,583,843,865]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallicus">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC7FF87FE309A2238379B5B" box="[432,583,843,865]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="348">T. metallicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The antebasal transverse impression on the pronotum is indistinct in the middle in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EFDCBFFC7FF87FEE09AE73BAC9BA6" authority="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath, 2009" authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" box="[352,476,904,926]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buddhai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC7FF87FEE09AE73BAC9BA6" box="[352,476,904,926]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="348">T. buddhai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A209E721FFC7FF87FE639AE738489BA5" box="[483,568,905,926]" pageId="22" pageNumber="348" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(but is stronger in the middle in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EFDCBFFC7FF87FECC9AC63B909B87" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1887" box="[332,480,935,957]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallicus">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC7FF87FECC9AC63B909B87" box="[332,480,935,957]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="348">T. metallicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EFDCBFFC7FF87FE799AC638A99B87" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1887" box="[505,729,935,957]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallicus">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC7FF87FE799AC638A99B87" box="[505,729,935,957]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="348">Tegyrius metallicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C4EFDCBFFC7FF87FE099AA8385A9BE0" authorityName="Prathapan &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Doeberl" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[393,554,966,987]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Tegyrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="keralaensis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93A5A5AFFC7FF87FE099AA8385A9BE0" box="[393,554,966,987]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="348">T. keralaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A209E721FFC7FF87FDB79AA838C39BE0" box="[567,691,966,988]" pageId="22" pageNumber="348" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the structure of the aedeagus, the spermatheca, and the male last abdominal ventrite.
